.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a Rust CLI tool for working with Claude Code and pi session logs.
It provides API and pi usage analysis, chart-focused graph commands,
MCP servers, and a security hook system for controlling which tools
and commands Claude Code can execute.
.Ss API Pricing
The
.Cm api\-pricing
subcommand analyzes Claude API usage from log directories
and generates detailed cost or token-count reports.
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl d , Fl \-dir Ar dir
Directory to analyze for API usage.
.It Fl \-timezone Ar local|utc
Timezone for date determination.
Default:
.Ar local .
.It Fl \-conversations
Aggregate by conversation/session instead of by date.
.It Fl \-tokens
Show token counts instead of dollar costs.
.It Fl \-start\-time Ar DATETIME
Start time filter in ISO 8601 format
.Pq e.g., 2025\-01\-01T00:00:00Z .
UTC is assumed if no timezone is specified.
.It Fl \-end\-time Ar DATETIME
End time filter in ISO 8601 format.
.El
.Ss Pi Cost
The
.Cm pi cost
subcommand analyzes pi session logs and generates either cost reports
or token-count reports using the same date and conversation grouping options
as
.Cm api\-pricing .
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl d , Fl \-dir Ar dir
Directory to analyze for pi session usage.
Default:
.Pa ~/.pi/agent/sessions .
.It Fl \-timezone Ar local|utc
Timezone for date determination.
Default:
.Ar local .
.It Fl \-conversations
Aggregate by conversation/session instead of by date.
.It Fl \-tokens
Show token counts instead of dollar costs.
.It Fl \-start\-time Ar DATETIME
Start time filter in ISO 8601 format.
UTC is assumed if no timezone is specified.
.It Fl \-end\-time Ar DATETIME
End time filter in ISO 8601 format.
.El
.Ss Graphs
The
.Cm graphs claude
and
.Cm graphs pi
subcommands render chart-focused stacked summaries for Claude/API and pi usage.
They accept the same timezone, conversation, token, and time-filter flags
as the corresponding table reports.
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm graphs claude Fl d Ar dir
Render Claude/API usage graphs from the given log directory.
.It Cm graphs pi Op Fl d Ar dir
Render pi usage graphs from the given session directory.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.pi/agent/sessions
when
.Fl \-dir
is omitted.
.El
.Ss MCP Servers
The
.Cm mcp
subcommand runs one of the built\-in Model Context Protocol servers
for read\-only git operations, read\-only jj operations, and project tools.
.Ss Project Approval
The
.Cm approve\-project
subcommand opens a TUI to approve the project\-configured tools and checks
defined in
.Pa .config/tools.toml
for the project\-tools MCP server.
.Ss Hooks
The
.Cm hooks exec
subcommand executes Claude Code hooks, reading input from stdin
and applying configured tool and bash rules.
This is the entry point used by Claude Code's hook system.
.Pp
The
.Cm hooks report
subcommand reads the JSON-lines hook logs from
.Pa ~/.local/state/moriarty/hooks/
.Pq or the directory given by the \-d / \-\-dir option
and prints a JSON report of recorded PreToolUse results, aggregated by the
exact tool, arguments, result, and deciding rule with a count per group.
Each row names the rule whose action produced the decision; the field is omitted
when no rule decided
.Pq passthrough, an unconfigured Ask, or a compound whose merged leaves matched no rule .
The
.Fl \-start\-time
and
.Fl \-end\-time
options restrict the report to a time range (ISO 8601; UTC when no offset is given),
.Fl \-tool
restricts it to a single tool name, and
.Fl \-result
restricts it to one outcome
.Pq Cm allow , deny , ask , modify , passthrough .
.Ss Test Commands
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm test project\-tools Op Ar project_dir
Run all configured project tools in parallel.
Defaults to the current directory.
.It Cm test checks Op Ar project_dir
Run all configured project checks in parallel.
.It Cm test bash\-rules Op Ar command
Test a bash command against configured rules.
If no command is provided, reads from stdin.
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl c , Fl \-config Ar path
Custom config file path.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.config/moriarty/tool_rules.toml .
.It Fl \-json
Output results as JSON instead of pretty\-printed text.
.It Fl \-explain
Show how the command splits into leaf commands, the normalized text and matching
rule for each leaf, and the merged decision the hook would make.
This reflects the real per\-leaf evaluation
.Pq see Xr moriarty\-bash\-rules 5 ;
the default
.Pq non\-explain
output reports the single\-command result and is unchanged.
.It Fl \-cwd Ar dir
Simulate the hook working directory for in\-cwd absolute\-path normalization.
Defaults to the process working directory.
.El
.El
.Ss Rules
The
.Cm rules
subcommands inspect, validate, and author the bash and tool rules in
.Pa ~/.config/moriarty/tool_rules.toml .
They never run the hook.
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm rules lint Op Fl \-strict
Report rules the hook silently ignores
.Pq dropped because of an undefined fragment, invalid regex, or incomplete field/pattern pair ,
exiting nonzero if any exist.
With
.Fl \-strict ,
additionally warn about likely\-shadowed and over\-broad Allow rules.
.It Cm rules list\-fragments
List the merged pattern fragments
.Pq built\-in defaults plus user\-defined ,
marking the source of each.
.It Cm rules schema
Print a canonical example
.Pa tool_rules.toml
covering every rule and action variant.
.It Cm rules starter
Print a paste\-ready set of allow\-rules for common read\-only commands, designed for
the per\-leaf engine.
.It Cm rules suggest
Suggest anchored rules for commands the hook frequently prompted on, mined from the
hook logs.
Each recorded command is first split into the leaf simple\-commands the hook actually
evaluates (normalized with the recorded working directory), so a compound like
.Ql git status && ls
yields one candidate per leaf and a leaf shared by several compounds accumulates their counts.
.Fl \-result
selects the recorded outcome to mine
.Pq Cm ask No or Cm deny ;
.Fl \-match Cm exact|prefix|fuzzy
chooses the generated pattern shape; and
.Fl \-action Cm ask|deny|allow
sets the action
.Pq Cm allow No is refused unless Fl \-match Cm exact .
.Cm exact
emits one fully\-literal, fully\-anchored pattern per leaf;
.Cm prefix
one program\-name pattern per program; and
.Cm fuzzy
one pattern per program that generalizes observed simple\-identifier subcommands into a
closed alternation
.Pq for example Ql ^cargo (build|check)(\es|$) ,
falling back to the program prefix when any observed leaf has a flag, path, or bare
invocation in subcommand position.
The suggestion lists every observed command it covers so the generalization is reviewable.
By default only log lines recorded under the rule set currently installed at
.Pa ~/.config/moriarty/tool_rules.toml
are mined, so suggestions reflect the rules in force;
.Fl \-rules\-hash
restricts to a specific rule\-set hash and
.Fl \-all\-rules
mines every recorded line regardless of which rules produced it.
.It Cm rules replay
Re\-evaluate recorded Bash decisions against a candidate
.Fl \-config
and report divergences.
With
.Fl \-result Cm allow
it exits nonzero if any previously auto\-approved command would no longer be allowed,
guarding migrations against lost auto\-approvals.
The
.Fl \-start\-time
and
.Fl \-end\-time
options bound the replay window
.Pq ISO 8601; UTC when no offset is given ,
so a long\-lived log need not be replayed in full.
By default replay considers only the decisions recorded under the rule set currently
installed at the default config path
.Pq the migration source, independent of the Fl \-config No candidate ,
so the baseline is coherent;
.Fl \-rules\-hash
pins a specific rule\-set hash and
.Fl \-all\-rules
replays every recorded line.
Each hook decision is stamped in the log with a hash of the effective rule set that
produced it, which is what these filters match.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ev XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for configuration files.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.config .
.It Ev XDG_STATE_HOME
Base directory for state files including logs.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.local/state .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa ~/.config/moriarty/tool_rules.toml
Tool and bash rules configuration file.
See
.Xr moriarty\-tool\-rules 5
and
.Xr moriarty\-bash\-rules 5 .
.It Pa ~/.local/state/moriarty/hooks/
Hook execution log directory (JSON lines, daily-rotated).
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr moriarty\-tool\-rules 5 ,
.Xr moriarty\-bash\-rules 5
